14/04/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Businessman Kiro Kirov was released shortly before midnight on Monday (April 13th), 18 days after his March 27th abduction, the interior ministry announced. The kidnappers left him in Gorna Banya, near Sofia, but he managed to find a nearby house and called his family to come get him, his son Ivan said. According to the daily Standart, Kirov's family paid 620,000 euros in ransom Saturday. (BTA, bTV, Standart, Focus - 13/04/09)
